Uh no never mind, it _does_ generate the descriptor. I selected the wrong wallet in the console. Pfew. So it's a pure UI issue, investigating...

Restarting Bitcoin Core does add Bech32m to the menu. Maybe some reference to the receive screen got borked in the passphrase dialogs? See #509.

@eriknylund if you're _not_ seeing Bech32m after a restart, are you sure you checked the "Descriptor" box (it's selected by default)? You can run `getwalletinfo` in the Console (make sure to select the correct wallet in the console too) and look if you see `"descriptors": true`. Only descriptor wallets have Taproot support.
